			<text>
			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="13">The main reasons for oil spills are shipping accidents (groundings, collisions, tanker incidents), bad weather (storms, hurricanes, gusts of wind, seaquakes, tropical cyclones, tornadoes, willy-willies, typhoons), intentional pollution or intentional acts of violence (routine tank cleaning, dumping of oily wastes, vandalism, terrorism, acts of war) and human errors.<br><br>The main sources of spilled oil are generally: crude oil tankers breaking, crashing or stranding, product carriers or barges wrecking, oil wells blowing up or oil pipelines breaking or leaking.</font></textformat>]]>
			</text>
