			<text>
			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="13">Other sources can be:<br>- incidents with production facilities (for instance when crude oil is changed into other products such as tar, asphalt, etc.)<br>- incidents with oil drilling vessels or oil platforms (oil rigs located in the sea or ocean pumping oil from deep in the seabed or ocean floor)<br>- incidents while lightering (moving oil from one vessel to another)<br>- natural seepage (when natural oil found in  he ground leaks up in the water)<br>- mystery spills (people dumping oil or chemicals on purpose)<br><br>To try to prevent and help to clean up oil spills, governments pass laws to prevent dumping and contamination.<br>Littoral states also provide adequate reception facilities for dirty ballast and other oily residues.</font></textformat>]]>
			</text>
